Frequently asked questions

Expand all

AT&T Dedicated Internet is our premier internet service that is ideal for virtually all sizes and types of businesses. It is a unshared connection thats used only by your business, with the fastest speeds (from 500Gbps to 1Tbps), proactive monitoring, and 100% uptime guaranteed or well credit your account.

AT&T Dedicated Internet access is perfect for businesses that require the fastest speeds available and protection from outages with world-class Service Level Agreements (SLAs) supported by 24/7 active monitoring. You can expect top performance for high-definition video conferencing, phone calls over the internet (VoIP), and crucial business activities that depend on a fast, reliable, dedicated internet connection.

We can help you find the perfect plan speed and features for your business. Call to speak with a business expert about your specific needs.

Symmetric speed means that upload and download speeds are the same, unlike asymmetric, where download speeds are traditionally faster than upload speeds. Symmetric speeds are crucial for applications that send and receive large amounts of data, such as high-definition video conferencing, multiple broadcasts or conferences which run simultaneously, file hosting and uploads, and large data set transmission between business locations.

AT&T Dedicated Internet access is broadly available. Youll find it in Puerto Rico, U.S. Virgin Islands, 46 countries, and the U.S.

AT&T Dedicated Internet service can be easily installed to work with your companys existing network. AT&T has the largest fiber footprint with fiber installation at more than 9 million locations. Get up and running in as little as ten days at 3 million nationwide fiber-ready business locations. 

AT&T offers built-in network security and a wide range of additional optional security services to help protect your companys sensitive data from cyberattacks, including: AT&T Dynamic Defense, Enterprise Traffic Protector, Zero Trust architecture, Secure Access Service Edge (SASE), Managed Extended Detection and Response (XDR), and Content Delivery Network (CDN) services.

View all security solutions.

With AT&T Dedicated Internet access, you can view your Domain Name System (DNS) threat events by name, severity, and more through your AT&T Business Center portal. To activate this no-charge monitoring feature, configure your local DNS server or Active Directory server to forward DNS queries to AT&T DNS.

Dedicated internet service is an unshared connection where each customer has their own dedicated port, giving you more speed and control. AT&T Dedicated Internet comes with strong Service Level Agreements (SLAs) that are supported by 24/7 active monitoring. Even during peak usage times, AT&T Dedicated Internet access delivers the same outstanding experience. Shared internet uses a shared connection, allowing multiple customers to use the same bandwidth at the same time, which can impact speed and performance.
